[p]And, as the jest did glance away from me,
[p]'Tis ten to one it maim'd you two outright.

Marry, peace it bodes, and love, and quiet life,
[p]An awful rule, and right supremacy;
[p]And, to be short, what not that's sweet and happy.

I would your duty were as foolish too;
[p]The wisdom of your duty, fair Bianca,
[p]Hath cost me a hundred crowns since supper-time!
